en:
Include all <a href = "https://eportugal.gov.pt/entidades/autoridade-para-as-condicoes-do-trabalho" target = "_BLANK_" >work-related accidents</a> (including commuting) where the employee missed 4 or more calendar days of work.

- Any fracture except for fingers of the hands or feet;
- Amputation of arm, hand, fingers, leg, or foot;
- Temporary or permanent loss of vision;
- Head or trunk injury causing brain damage or damage to internal organs of the chest or abdomen;
- Any burn (including scalding) that: Affects more than 10% of the body; or Causes significant damage to the eyes, respiratory system, or other vital organs;
- Any degree of scalp injury requiring hospital treatment;
- Loss of consciousness caused by head injury or asphyxiation; or
- Any other damage resulting from work in confined spaces that:
- Leads to hypothermia, hyperthermia; or
- Loss of consciousness requiring resuscitation.
